         "bug": "The getFraction method does not handle the case where the numerator is Integer.MIN_VALUE and the denominator is negative. It throws an ArithmeticException in this case, but it would be better to handle this case explicitly and return a valid Fraction instance.",
         "severity": "Low",
         "location": "getFraction method"
      },
      {
         "bug": "The getFraction method does not check for overflow when creating the Fraction instance. If the numerator or denominator is too large, it may cause an ArithmeticException to be thrown. It would be better to check for overflow explicitly and handle it accordingly.",
         "severity": "Low",
         "location": "getFraction method"
      },
      {
         "bug": "The class does not implement the equals and hashCode methods correctly. The equals method should compare the numerators and denominators of the two fractions, and the hashCode method should return a hash code based on the numerators and denominators. However, the current implementation only compares the references of the two fractions.",
         "severity": "High",
         "location": "equals and hashCode methods"
